The paper deals with score-based structure discovery in Bayesian networks, which is a problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses time-space tradeoffs, which is a topic in algorithms and complexity theory (cs.DS). The use of recurrence relations and parallelization techniques also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents empirical results, which is a common feature of papers in the machine learning and data mining subfield (cs.LG).
